comments.message:
Aside from the `length` argument and switching the current `length` local to `measured`, I think the only other thing we need is the underflow check here before the subtraction on line 1041:

```
if (ctx->remaining < INTMAX_MIN + measured) {
    return pldm_msgbuf_status(ctx, EOVERFLOW);
}
```

Regarding the `length` argument, we then do:

```
if (length) {
    *length = measured;
}
```
